net.sf.jdivelog.ci
Interface ComputerInterface

All Known Implementing Classes:
AladinInterface, DR5UddfInterface, OSTCInterface, SmartInterface, SuuntoInterface
public interface ComputerInterface

This interface describes all necessary functions to implement a computer interface.

Author:
Pascal Pellmont

getPropertyNames

java.lang.String[] getPropertyNames()
gets the name of the properties that can be set in the configuration dialog. the name of the properties should start with the name of the computer interface, e.g. suunto.xxx

a String array containing the property names.

transfer

void transfer(StatusInterface statusInterface,
              JDiveLog logbook)
              throws TransferException,
                     NotInitializedException,
                     InvalidConfigurationException
reads the data out of the divecomputer.

Parameters:
statusInterface - The interface to show progress information to the user.
logbook - The actual opened logbook
Throws:
TransferException - if an error occured during transfer of the data from the dive computer.
NotInitializedException - if initialized has not been called before.
InvalidConfigurationException - if the configuration has an error, e.g. the specified interface doesn't exist, or the wrong computer is attached.

getDives

java.util.TreeSet<JDive> getDives()
gets the transferred dives.

Returns:
a TreeSet containing the JDives. Returns an empty TreeSet if no dives have been transferred.
